# create new app (ios + android ready)
flutter-new myapp --org com.sizelove --platforms ios,android

cd myapp

# run on simulator
open -a Simulator
flutter run -d "iPhone 16 Plus"

# run on web
flutter run -d chrome

# list all devices (sim, chrome, android, etc.)
flutter devices

# clean & rebuild (if something feels off)
flutter clean
(cd ios && pod install)

######
mobile_align.sh
######
Notes / gotchas it covers
	•	iOS
	•	Removes ios/.gitignore (the old template that hid Generated.xcconfig)
	•	Rewrites ios/Flutter/*.xcconfig with the canonical 2-line includes
	•	Sets Runner → Base Configuration to those xcconfigs
	•	Creates a minimal Podfile if missing
	•	Runs pod install
	•	Force-adds Podfile + xcconfigs so future clones don’t break
	•	Android
	•	Ensures JDK 17 (prints Java version, tries to set JAVA_HOME on macOS)
	•	Ensures Android SDK path and writes android/local.properties
	•	Installs core SDK components with sdkmanager (if present)
	•	Precaches Android artifacts for the active Flutter version
	•	Keeps local.properties ignored in Git
